        "username": "WonkyTappet",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/w/d9b06d/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2022-01-18T18:21:15.024Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hello!</p>\n<p>Throwing in a vote for the return of captions on images (particularly images sent in bulk) please!</p>\n<p>If I send a batch of photos in one go, I‚Äôd like to be able to send them with a general message (which can currently be done) but put individual captions on each image sent with that message. It‚Äôs currently possible to add text by effectively drawing over the image, but that modifies the image sent, rather than being a caption for that image.</p>\n<p>Used to be a feature, but looks to have been retired? I know it vanished from the Android beta around Sept 2021 and has since been removed from the desktop app (Linux, 5.28.0). I don‚Äôt believe there‚Äôs anything currently open about this - all I can find is an issue (11882) raised against the Android app on Github which seems to suggest it was deliberately removed - <a href=\"https://github.com/signalapp/Signal-Android/issues/11882\" class=\"inline-onebox\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Subtexts to images is not possible anymore on Android version ¬∑ Issue #11882 ¬∑ signalapp/Signal-Android ¬∑ GitHub</a></p>\n<p>Hopefully this is the right forum to belatedly throw in my support for the return of the feature - I dropped an email over in back in 2021 when I first spotted it, but while I can remember putting a bunch of screenshots together for a response, I can‚Äôt find anything other than the initial reply from Signal support - any number of reasons for that, but they all boil down to the effect of me failing to follow it up! (Whoops‚Ä¶)</p>\n<p>Rich</p>",
