        "created_at": "2026-01-27T08:05:09.925Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Took a while to find, but I knew someone else must have requested this feature or something similar and one of the replies even notes one of my usecases; a travel log!</p>\n<p>I‚Äôd settle for not having actual captions perse, rather adding the ability to give each individual image it‚Äôs own message rather than bundling it all into one generic message is ok too. This functionality is already used in other messaging platforms by one or two of my family members for their travel logs where describing the image context helps other familymembers understand what‚Äôs going on in the photo.</p>\n<p>The current cumbersome workaround is to send each image individually, but I sporadically see people just defaulting back to another messaging platform citing \"it takes too long‚Äù or ‚Äúit‚Äôs too difficult‚Äù on signal.</p>",
